'''β-Eleostearic acid''', or '''(9''E'',11''E'',13''E'')-octadeca-9,11,13-trienoic acid''', is an [[organic compound]] with formula {{chem|C|18|H|30|O|2}} or H<sub>3</sub>C-(-CH<sub>2</sub>-)<sub>3</sub>(-CH=CH-)<sub>3</sub>-(-CH<sub>2</sub>-)<sub>7</sub>-(C=O)OH.  It is the all-''trans'' [[conformational isomer]] of [[octadecatrienoic acid]].

==See also==
* [[alpha-eleostearic acid|α-Eleostearic acid]], the (9''Z'',11''E'',13''E'')-isomer, found in [[tung oil]] and [[bitter gourd]] seed oil.

