[[File:Logan County wind farm from US 136.jpg|thumb|Eastern portion of the farm]]
The '''Rail Splitter Wind Farm''' is a 67-turbine wind farm in northern [[Logan County, Illinois|Logan County]] and southern [[Tazewell County, Illinois|Tazewell County]] in the U.S. state of Illinois. The turbines are expected to generate a maximum of 100.5 [[megawatt]]s of electricity. The wind farm is owned and operated by [[Horizon Wind Energy]]. The [[wind turbine]]s that constitute the farm are centered on the town of [[Emden, Illinois|Emden]] on both sides of [[Interstate 155 (Illinois)|Interstate 155]]. The wind farm, constructed in 2008-2009 at a cost of $200.0 million, was dedicated on July 21, 2009.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.sj-r.com/features/x2038868789/Rail-Splitter-Wind-Farm-by-the-numbers
| title= Rail Splitter Wind Farm by the numbers | publisher= (Springfield, IL) [[State Journal-Register]] | date = 2009-01-30 | accessdate = 2009-07-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.pantagraph.com/news/local/article_d3b1c746-7661-11de-b561-001cc4c002e0.html
| title=Lincoln's 1858 speech cited at ribbon-cutting of newest wind farm| publisher=(Bloomington, IL) [[The Pantagraph|Pantagraph]] | date = 2009-07-22 | accessdate = 2009-08-03}}</ref>

