The '''Society for [[Cryobiology]]''' is an international scientific society that was founded in 1964. Its objectives are to promote research in low temperature [[biology]], to improve scientific understanding in this field, and to disseminate and aid in the application of this knowledge. The Society also publishes a [[Academic journal|journal]] called ''Cryobiology''.
Although some members of the Society for Cryobiology encouraged or helped in the development of early-stage [[cryonics]] in the 1960s, the Society later on banned cryonicists from becoming members.<ref name="cryobiology">{{cite news | url = http://www.alcor.org/Library/html/coldwar.html | last = Darwin | first = Mike | work = Cryonics | year = 1991 | publisher = Alcor Life Extension Foundation | accessdate = 2009-08-24 | title = Cold War: The Conflict Between Cryonicists and Cryobiologists }}</ref>
